xt":" "},{"text":"connection call ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_close()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and give up your"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reference. Note that the other peer may disconnect at any time -","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a typical thing to do when accepting a connection is to listen to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the [DBusConnection](\/\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnection\/onclosed(flags:handler:) signal."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusServer","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" contains "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"runInThread"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then the signal is emitted in a new thread dedicated to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"connection. Otherwise the signal is emitted in the thread-default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"main context (see [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"text":"])","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the thread that ","type":"text"},{"code":"server","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" was constructed in."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You are guaranteed that signal handlers for this signal runs","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"before incoming messages on "},{"code":"connection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are processed. This means"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that it’s suitable to call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_register_object()"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"similar from the signal handler."}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This represents the u